HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 930
By Salinas
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Dominican Sister of
Peace Marina Gibbons, OP.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Dominican Sister of Peace Marina Gibbons, OP; and
WHEREAS, a native of Chicago, Illinois, Sister Marina devoted seventy-nine years of
her life to religious vocation, education, and service as a member of the Dominican Sisters of
Peace, leaving a legacy marked by intellectual rigor, compassion, and leadership; and
WHEREAS, Sister Marina Gibbons was a lifelong scholar, earning a Bachelor of Arts
degree in English, Philosophy, and History from Manhattan College, a Master of Arts degree in
Library Science from Rosary College, and a Doctor of Philosophy degree in English Literature
from St. Louis University; and
WHEREAS, she ministered as a teacher at numerous institutions of learning, including
Resurrection in Brooklyn, New York; Mount Trinity Academy in Watertown, Massachusetts; Rust
College in Holly Springs, Mississippi; and Brooklyn College in Brooklyn, New York, sharing her
love of literature and learning with generations of students; and
WHEREAS, Sister Marina provided distinguished educational leadership in Tennessee,
serving as teacher, academic dean, and president of Siena College in Memphis and later as
superintendent and president of St. Agnes/St. Dominic in Memphis, a role she assumed in 1978
and held for many years; and
WHEREAS, her service extended beyond the United States, and in 1994, Sister Marina
Gibbons traveled to Vietnam, where she taught English in Ho Chi Minh City and surrounding
areas, further reflecting her commitment to global education and cross-cultural engagement;
and
