WHEREAS, from 1996 to 2001, Sister Marina served as vice president and academic
dean of St. Catharine College in St. Catharine, Kentucky, and from 2002 until the college's
closing in 2016, she continued to serve generously as a volunteer in numerous capacities, while
also providing community service at the St. Catharine Motherhouse; and
WHEREAS, Sister Marina Gibbons also served on the former leadership team of the
Dominican Sisters of St. Catharine, offering wisdom and guidance shaped by decades of
experience and faith-filled service; and
WHEREAS, in 2020, she moved to Sansbury Care Center, where she entered a final
ministry of prayer and presence, continuing to serve others through quiet witness and devotion;
and
WHEREAS, Sister Marina Gibbons is survived by several nieces and nephews and will
be remembered with gratitude by countless students, colleagues, and communities whose lives
were enriched by her leadership and care; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we remember the bountiful life of this exceptional human
being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Dominican Sister of Peace Marina Gibbons, OP,
reflecting fondly upon her impeccable character and her stalwart commitment to living the
examined life with courage and conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we express our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family of Sister Marina Gibbons, OP.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
